metatags.og:title: How to Reduce Heart Rate
metatags.og:description: The average adult has a resting heart rate between 60 and 100 beats per minute. A trained athlete is likely to have a heart rate as low as 40 to 60 beats per minute. Generally, a lower heart rate is desirable because it indicates that your heart is functioning efficiently. There are several ways in which you can lower your heart rate.
